{
  "texts": [
    "The results indicate that the proposed scheme is suitable for cloud and blockchain applications.Through theoretical security analyses, the proposed scheme is compared to various aspects of schemes reported in previous studies in the literature in terms of scalability, confidentially, integrity, availability, SPOF avoidance, and resistance.",
    "It is demonstrated that it is strong against manin-the-middle, impersonation, and modification attacks, it meets the intended security requirements, and it is more advantageous than those reported in the other studies that are discussed.The proposed scheme is also designed so that it can be applied to data in different areas.",
    "It is planned to be applicable to different areas such as banking, finance, and real estate in future studies.",
    "As a result of the comparison of different consensus mechanisms, a suitable consensus mechanism will be selected according to the usage area.",
    "The proposed scheme will also be designed to be integrated with features such as machine learning and artificial intelligence depending on different areas of usage.Fig. 11Fig."
  ]
}